abstract: Russian troops are engaging in standoffs with U.S. troops guarding oil fields and fighting remnants of the Islamic State.
snippet: Russian troops are engaging in standoffs with U.S. troops guarding oil fields and fighting remnants of the Islamic State.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Russia is intensifying a pressure campaign on U.S. military forces in northeastern Syria following the American withdrawal from much of that area ahead of a Turkish cross-border offensive last fall, American military and diplomatic officials say.

abstract: Unbowed by a public rebuke from his attorney general, President Donald Trump says he has the "legal right" to intervene in criminal cases and sidestep the Justice Department's historic independence. At the same time, it was revealed federal prosecutors have been ordered to review the criminal case of his former national security adviser.
snippet: Unbowed by a public rebuke from his attorney general, President Donald Trump says he has the "legal right" to intervene in criminal cases and sidestep the Justice Department's historic independence. At the same time, it was revealed federal prosec...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Unbowed by a public rebuke from his attorney general, President Donald Trump says he has the "legal right" to intervene in criminal cases and sidestep the Justice Department's historic independence. At the same time, it was revealed federal prosecutors have been ordered to review the criminal case of his former national security adviser.
headline_main: Trump Doesn't Heed Barr's Request to Cool Tweeting on DOJ
headline_print_headline: Trump Doesn't Heed Barr's Request to Cool Tweeting on DOJ

abstract: A whipsaw week of charged decisions by the Justice Department, some favored by the president and others not, has bewildered much of Washington.
snippet: A whipsaw week of charged decisions by the Justice Department, some favored by the president and others not, has bewildered much of Washington.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Trump learned that the Justice Department was dropping a case against a former F.B.I. official whom he considered one of his longtime enemies, his immediate response was anger. As he flipped on the television Friday and watched how the story was being covered, that anger only mounted.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo arrives in Africa this weekend as the first U.S. cabinet official to visit in more than 18 months, and he is certain to face questions about the U.S. military's future on the continent and new U.S. visa restrictions against millions of Africans.
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo arrives in Africa this weekend as the first U.S. cabinet official to visit in more than 18 months, and he is certain to face questions about the U.S. military's future on the continent and new U.S. visa restrictions ...
lead_paragraph: DAKAR, Senegal — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo arrives in Africa this weekend as the first U.S. cabinet official to visit in more than 18 months, and he is certain to face questions about the U.S. military's future on the continent and new U.S. visa restrictions against millions of Africans.
headline_main: US Secretary of State Heads to Africa After Long Absence
headline_print_headline: US Secretary of State Heads to Africa After Long Absence

abstract: Planning for changes to the estate tax and the valuation discount for small businesses can be challenging. Here’s how to take advantage of them now.
snippet: Planning for changes to the estate tax and the valuation discount for small businesses can be challenging. Here’s how to take advantage of them now.
lead_paragraph: Trying to guess how and when the tax code is going to change and plan for those changes now is an impossible task.

abstract: Shares of Nvidia Corp rose 6% on Friday after the chipmaker stunned analysts with strong quarterly results and joined rivals Intel Corp and Advanced Micro Devices Inc in predicting strong demand for chips used in the latest generation of data centers and AI.
snippet: Shares of Nvidia Corp rose 6% on Friday after the chipmaker stunned analysts with strong quarterly results and joined rivals Intel Corp and Advanced Micro Devices Inc in predicting strong demand for chips used in the latest generation of data cent...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Shares of Nvidia Corp rose 6% on Friday after the chipmaker stunned analysts with strong quarterly results and joined rivals Intel Corp and Advanced Micro Devices Inc in predicting strong demand for chips used in the latest generation of data centers and AI.
headline_main: Nvidia Shares Surge on Signs of Machine Learning Boom
headline_print_headline: Nvidia Shares Surge on Signs of Machine Learning Boom

abstract: Nevada is more diverse than Iowa and in many ways more reflective of the Democratic Party. And it has a different take on how caucuses should work.
snippet: Nevada is more diverse than Iowa and in many ways more reflective of the Democratic Party. And it has a different take on how caucuses should work.
lead_paragraph: After the chaos in Iowa, Nevada Democrats want to show the country what a caucus should look like.
